abstract: Commerce and Labor Departments reports on investments and new jobless benefits suggest that American economy is on upswing; Labor Dept reports weekly claims for unemployment benefits rose 3,000 to seasonally adjusted 267,000.
lead_paragraph: Reports from the Commerce and Labor Departments on investments and new jobless benefits suggested the resilience of American economic growth.

headline.main: Economic Growth in U.S. Poised to Last, Data Suggest
headline.print_headline: Growth in U.S. Poised to Last, Data Suggests

snippet: Reports from the Commerce and Labor Departments on investments and new jobless benefits suggested the resilience of American economic growth.
